In a statement Health Department spokesperson Desmond Motha said that the MEC s intervention would ensure that all bodies that require burial would be examined by the weekend.He said staff members had feigned illness. This follows the disruption of services at Park Rynie Mortuary where the bulk of the staff have not reported for duty claiming to be sick he said."MEC Dhlomo is a forensic pathology practitioner by profession and has cancelled all his scheduled duties to partake in the performance of post-mortems on bodies that need to be released Motha said. We have now transferred all the bodies from the Park Rynie facility to Port Shepstone mortuary where eight post-mortems will be performed today and the rest in the coming days he added. - TMG Digital/The Times